    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Forms branching yellowish-brown to almost black blades that emerge from a small holdfast. Edges of the blades, and sometimes the surfaces, bear numerous small, branched outgrowths (hence common name). May also incorporate swollen gas-filled bladders.</p><p>Becomes black and papery when exposed to air and dries out at low tide.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_7781",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Up to about 300 mm tall.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_7782",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Southern African endemic.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u><i> </i>Namibia to about East London.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_7783",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>Fairly distinctive and common species found in patches on intertidal rocks, particularly in sand-inundated areas.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_7784",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Photosynthetic.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_7785",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>The familiar form is the gametophyte and the sporophyte phase is crustose and capable of surviving long periods buried in sand.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_7786",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>The outgrowths along the edges of the blades are a fairly distinctive identification feature.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_7787",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Further reading / References",
